   performedsignificantly better than GPT 3.5 across all metrics. The
   fine-tuned LLaMA 2 with a small FM performed better than GPT 3.5(even
   with RAG) in returning references with the answers. Conclusions: The
   study shows that a reliable and accessible CaLM can be developed using
   small FMs with a knowledge basespecific to the caregiving domain},
